{{Quote|You can buy a bio-cocoon from Dendratis Exports for 2,000 credits, but remember: the bio-cocoon is a restricted biological hazard.|Chentu Chek, ''Bounty Hunters Guild Handbook''|<ref name="BHC">''[[The Bounty Hunter Code: From the Files of Boba Fett]]''</ref>}}
'''Dendratis Biological Exports, Incorporated''', also known as '''Dendratis Exports''', manufactured the wild animal trap known as the [[bio-cocoon]]. The technology allowed for the incapacitation or [[Death/Legends|killing]] of its entrapped target and was classified as a biological hazard. The company and its product were featured in the ''[[Bounty Hunters Guild Handbook]]'' as well as in ''[[Galladinium's Galactic Datalog of Fantastic Technology]]''.

==Description==
[[File:Biococoon-TBHC.jpg|thumb|right|220px|Dendratis Biological Exports, Incorporated manufactured the bio-cocoon.]]
Dendratis Biological Exports, Incorporated,<ref name="Galladinium" /> alternatively referred to as Dendratis Exports,<ref name="BHC" /> was a company that manufactured the [[bio-cocoon]] trap, sold for two thousand [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]].<ref name="Galladinium" /> A square [[Plastic/Legends|plastic]] sheet, it made use of one<ref name="BHC" /> or two cultures of microscopic organisms<ref name="Galladinium" />&mdash;[[kivilol spore]]s in one variant&mdash;to entrap a target that stepped on it<ref name="BHC" />&mdash;incapacitating it in one variant<ref name="Galladinium" /> but potentially also being [[Death/Legends|lethal]] in another.<ref name="BHC" /> The bio-cocoon was registered as a wild animal trap and was popular among [[Big game hunter/Legends|big-game hunters]],<ref name="Galladinium" /> although its usage was also restricted due to it being a biological hazard.<ref name="BHC" />

==History==
At one point between [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]] and [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]],<ref name="BHCDate">''[[The Bounty Hunter Code: From the Files of Boba Fett]]'' includes an [[in-universe]] copy of the ''[[Bounty Hunters Guild Handbook]]''. The included edition of the Handbook was published at some point following the [[Declaration of a New Order|establishment]] of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and is annotated by [[Greedo/Legends|Greedo]], whose [[Death/Legends|death]] is depicted in {{Film|IV}}. Since ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' places the formation of the Empire and the events of ''A New Hope'' that included Greedo's death in [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]] and [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]], respectively, the included edition of the Bounty Hunters' Guild Handbook must have therefore been published at some point between those two dates.</ref> [[Armory Master]] [[Chentu Chek]] of the [[Bounty Hunters' Guild/Legends|Bounty Hunters' Guild]] mentioned Dendratis Biological Exports, Incorporated and the bio-cocoon in a chapter of the Updated Imperial Edition of the ''[[Bounty Hunters Guild Handbook]]'' dedicated to various [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] equipment,<ref name="BHC" /> of which the bio-cocoon was an example. The company was also noted in the entry for the bio-cocoon in the [[Galladinium's 50th anniversary edition|fiftieth-anniversary edition]] of ''[[Galladinium's Galactic Datalog of Fantastic Technology]]'',<ref name="Galladinium" /> published at some point between [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]] and [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]].<ref name="GalladiniumDate">''[[Galladinium's Fantastic Technology]]'' is set during the [[Time/Legends|time]] period between the events of {{Film|IV}} and {{Film|V}}, which corresponds to some point between [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]] and [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]], according to ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''.</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
Dendratis Biological Exports, Incorporated was introduced in ''[[Galladinium's Fantastic Technology]]'', a [[1995]] sourcebook authored by [[Rick D. Stuart]] for use with [[West End Games]]' ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]''.<ref name="Galladinium" /> The [[2013]] book ''[[The Bounty Hunter Code: From the Files of Boba Fett]]'', which was authored by [[Daniel Wallace]], [[Jason Fry]], and [[Ryder Windham]], introduced the alternate name "Dendratis Exports" for the company.<ref name="BHC" />

